In Java IDE like IntelliJ, if you hover a method defintion, right-click on it, you can `find usages`: this will look for calls to this method in the entire projet.

It would be great to have such a function as peek, like `peek usages`.

So if you have:

```js
// foo.js
class foo {
   bar() {
    }
}
```

```js
// bar.js
class bar {
   constructor() {
      this.foo = new foo();
      this.foo.bar();
    }
}
```

```js
// animal.js
class animal {
   constructor() {
    }
    yell() {
      let foo = new foo();
      foo.bar();
   }
}
```

Calling `peek usages` on the `bar()` line would show one usage of this method: into the bar.js file, line 5 and animal.js line 7.
